      "content": "that makes sense. it just feels like the people pushing these laws don't really get how things work in a small town. they see big numbers and think it's all great, but they don't realize it might actually kill the local shops. do you think there's a way to look at this that isn't just 'increase wages for dignity' vs 'keep them low to save jobs'? or is one side just fundamentally more realistic for a business owner like me?",
